  "text": "An SSD-style detector [CITATION_1] works by adding a sequence of feature maps of progressively decreasing spatial resolution to an image classification network such as VGG [CITATION_2] . These feature layers replace the last few layers of the image classification network, and 3x3 and 1x1 convolutional filters are used to transform one feature map to the next along with max-pooling. See Fig. 3 for a depiction of the model.",
